<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-26T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="491" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4493: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-26T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 26,
                                        1922—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>156. Your 285, June 25, 6 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Department is unwilling that Consul at Canton should participate in any
                            plan of mediation. Your views in this regard have the Department’s
                            unqualified approval.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>